body.description: The instinctive action of sucking helps to calm and soothe babies and all parents know theres nothing more wonderful than a calm, content baby. So, when you need to turn screams and sobs into smiles and sleep, simply pick up a Tommee Tippee Fun Style pacifier. As the symmetrical silicone baglet is fully reversible, there is no wrong side-up so the pacifier will always be placed correctly in your babys mouth, even when they put it in their mouth themselves. The curved shield sits comfortably between babys chin and nose and the holes in each side allow extra air flow and prevent the build-up of moisture which helps to protect babys delicate skin against irritation. The BPA-free silicone baglet is soft and flexible whilst also being robust and durable. The smooth surface of silicone is very easy to clean and wont absorb stains and odors. Simply pop in a sterilizer, wash by hand or in the dishwasher. We recommend against prolonged pacifier use over 24 months and stopping pacifier use when your child is older than 36 months. *From an independent study in July 2021 of 416 moms with a 0-36m child, who are currently using a Tommee Tippee pacifier: *99% of moms would recommend a Tommee Tippee pacifier *97% of moms say a Tommee Tippee pacifier helped settle baby *93% of moms say babies love their Tommee Tippee pacifier *97.5% of babies accept a Tommee Tippee pacifier Warning! Do not tie pacifier around childs neck as it presents a strangulation danger.

Available in different age stages Our 0-6-m size features a smaller nipple and shield for tiny mouths and noses. As your baby grows, we recommend you move up through the age stages to the 6-18m and 18-36m pacifiers which offer the same benefits but with larger nipples and shields. Easy to clean & BPA free Silicone is taste-free and won’t retain any stains or odors. Easy to clean either in a sterilizer, by hand or in the top rack of the dishwasher. Always BPA and phthalate-free for your ultimate reassurance.

Can I use a pacifier while breastfeeding? Yes of course. All Tommee Tippee pacifiers feature symmetrical nipples which closely resemble the natural shape of a mother’s nipple, therefore reducing the risk of confusion between nipple and pacifier. All Tommee Tippee pacifiers are suitable for use from birth but you should consult medical advice regarding when to introduce a pacifier to your baby if you are breastfeeding. How often should I replace my baby’s pacifier? In the interests of hygiene, we recommend that you change your baby’s pacifier every month. Always check the pacifier before each use and replace at the first signs of damage or weakness. We recommend against prolonged pacifier use over 24 months and stopping pacifier use when your child is older than 36 months.
